SIMPLE: enact
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enact
<hw>En*act"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Enacted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Enacting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To decree; to
establish by legal and authoritative act; to make into a law;
especially, to perform the legislative act with reference to (a bill)
which gives it the validity of law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To act; to perform; to do; to effect.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The king <qex>enacts</qex> more wonders than a man.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To act the part of; to represent; to play.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I did <qex>enact</qex> Julius Caesar.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Enacting clause</b></col>, <cd>that clause of a bill
which formally expresses the legislative sanction.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enact</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Enact
<hw>En*act"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Purpose; determination.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enactive</ent>⟦br⟧
